{"ts":"2026-07-11T02:49:38.183Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-0mjz"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-504: importer/exporter registered without options yields an unusable CLI command (no arg/flag contracts)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"When an extension registers an importer/exporter with only a handler — api.registerImporter('todos', handler) — and omits the optional options argument, the derived '<name> import'/'<name> export' CLI command is completely unusable: positional args are rejected ('Too many arguments'), every flag is rejected ('Unknown option'), and --help shows no flags and no <file> arg. The same handler works via the SDK/MCP action path (runAction with options). Nothing warns the author at registration, doctor has no diagnostic, and the runtime errors give an agent no actionable hint. Adjacent to GH-503 (pm-s9iu) but a distinct code path: here the CANONICAL derived command of an installed importer/exporter carries no contract at all. Candidate remedies from the issue: pass-through/permissive arg mode for contract-less importer commands, a registration-time or doctor warning, and an error hint pointing at the SDK action path."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","cli","extensions","gh-issue","sdk"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-11T02:49:38.183Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-11T02:49:38.183Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":120},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"Bare importer/exporter registrations produce a usable CLI command (positional file arg + generic flag pass-through) OR registration/doctor surfaces an actionable warning and the runtime error names the missing-options cause and the working SDK action path; regression test covers a handler-only registerImporter fixture; GH-504 closed with a comment linking the fix"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-s9iu","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-11T02:49:38.183Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"9c0fde20a501687fb7100a12751d792b35c45f3db3e4a2f6c1c1adb6a2372b62","message":""}
